&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time post 37.5 hours per week – Band 5 Development / Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you want to be part of a well-supported, hard-working, highly appreciated team?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you enthusiastic, dedicated and up for a challenging yet rewarding role? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Yes?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting and rare opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Care Co-Ordinator working within the Early Intervention in Psychosis Team based at Parkway Centre. The role involves working across the East Hampshire area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Early Intervention in Psychosis team are diverse and full of talented individuals, offering a wide range of specialities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The work is varied and interesting and there is a strong team approach ensuring good support for the successful applicant. The role requires lone working, use of initiative and a commitment to team working and service user empowerment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There will be an opportunity to develop your skills working in a specialist team and to increase your knowledge of working with psychosis.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be from a mental health nursing background and will need to be able to work flexibly and to demonstrate experience of the CPA process, risk assessment, and the recovery model. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post may involve weekend and bank holiday working on a rota basis as per service user need and a valid driving licence and access to vehicle for work purposes is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mental health nursing graduates will be considered for a development post depending on experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;SHFT are an equal opportunities employer and welcome applications from all who believe they fit the essential requirements for this role regardless of their race, sex, disability, religion/belief, sexual orientation or age.**However exemption is claimed under the Equality Act 2010 Part 1 Schedule 9 and applications can only be accepted from males due to the care needs of the MALE residents/patients**&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Happy to talk flexible working&lt;/strong&gt;-&lt;strong&gt; all requests for flexible and part time working will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
